(fifthQuint)Comparison of Time-restricted Feeding and Continuous Feeding in Critically Ill Patients.

 Enteral nutrition support can be administered by continuous administration or by time-restricted administration in ICU.

 Continuous feeding is the most popular feeding schedule because of its less nursing burden and reducing the aspiration prevalence theoretically.

 However, previous studies demonstrated that there was no complications (diarrhea, distension, Ventilator associated pneumonia-VAP incidence, and so on) difference between these two feeding schedule.

