 However, time-restricted feeding is more physical than continuous feeding.

 In ICU, the disorder of protein synthesis is a universal problem and is associated with ICU acquired weakness.

 In some animal researches, time-restricted feeding was proved to have a greater stimulatory effect on protein synthesis than continuous feeding.

 Besides of light, time-restricted feeding can adjust the biological rhythms.

 It is known that biological clocks could affect energy metabolism, emotion and so on.

 In the "zi wu liu zhu" theory of traditional chinese medicine, feeding time should be at 7:00-9:00, 11:00-13:00 and 17:00-19:00.

 So researchers designed the study to compare the time-restricted feeding according to traditional chinese medicine and continuous feeding effect(especially protein synthesis) on ICU patients.

